# ROCEV Workflow Baseline

Use this project rule when discussing RTL, TB, simulation, coverage, formal, or
signoff work:

```text
Requirement -> Obligation -> Contract -> Evidence -> Validation
```

This is not a Cursor Skill. It is the working standard.

## Meaning

| Term | Plain meaning | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Requirement | What we want | FIFO preserves order |
| Obligation | Small thing the design must do | first pushed item is first popped |
| Contract | How it can be judged | expected model + scoreboard compare |
| Evidence | What actually exists on disk | results.xml, scoreboard row, coverage, VCD |
| Validation | Decision from evidence | closed / not closed / needs more evidence |

## Completion rule

Do not say a hardware task is done from model confidence.

Use this shape instead:

```text
Requirement:
Obligation:
Contract:
Evidence:
Validation:
```

If one field is missing, say it is missing.

## Examples

### RTL change

```text
Requirement:
  <ip> implements the required behavior for <case>.

Obligation:
  When <condition> occurs, RTL must produce <expected output/state>.

Contract:
  RTL compile/lint must pass, and the expected model or checker defines the
  expected output/state for this case.

Evidence:
  rtl/rtl_compile.json
  lint/dut_lint.json
  sim/scoreboard_events.jsonl

Validation:
  PASS only if compile/lint pass and the matching scoreboard/checker row passes.
```

### TB change

```text
Requirement:
  The testbench must observe <case>.

Obligation:
  At least one scenario drives <condition> and checks <expected behavior>.

Contract:
  Scenario list and scoreboard goals include this obligation.

Evidence:
  tb/cocotb/* test
  sim/scoreboard_events.jsonl
  cov/coverage.json

Validation:
  PASS only if the test ran, the scoreboard row exists, and coverage shows the case.
```

### Formal check

```text
Requirement:
  A safety invariant must hold for all legal states.

Obligation:
  <bad condition> must never produce <forbidden output/state>.

Contract:
  SVA property states the invariant.

Evidence:
  verify/protocol_assertions.sva
  verify/formal_status.json
  proof log

Validation:
  PASS only for the property that was actually proven.
```
